TITLE: Error Handling with Keychain Module's Discriminated Union
DESCRIPTION: Shows how to handle errors using the keychain module's discriminated union return type. Demonstrates type-safe access to values and handling specific error types without using optional chaining or try/catch blocks.
SOURCE: https://github.com/rainbow-me/rainbow/blob/develop/src/keychain/README.md#2025-04-19_snippet_1

LANGUAGE: typescript
CODE:
```
const { value, error } = await keychain.getObject('my-object');

if (value) {
   console.log(value.foo) // safe property access
} else {
   switch(error) {
      case(keychain.ErrorType.Unavailable):
      case(keychain.ErrorType.UserCanceled):
      case(keychain.ErrorType.NotAuthenticated):
         console.log(...)
         break;
      case(keychain.ErrorType.Unknown):
      default:
         console.log(`An unknown error occurred: ${error}`)
   }
}
```

